<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">25</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">5</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Sep 1 2005</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1255</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1276</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16160110/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16160110</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2005.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Sep 1 2005</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.255045721">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ECG+%3D+electrocardiographic&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ECG = electrocardiographic</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IR+%3D+inversion+recovery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IR = inversion recovery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SE+%3D+spin+echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SE = spin echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SSFP+%3D+steady-state+free+precession&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SSFP = steady-state free precession</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The techniques of cardiac MR imaging and the MR imaging findings of primary cardiac tumors, secondary cardiac tumors, and mimics of cardiac tumors are reviewed.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Patrick J.</span> <span property="familyName">Sparrow</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the British Heart Foundation Cardiac MRI Unit, Room 170, D Floor, Jubilee Wing, The General Infirmary, Leeds LS1 3EX, England. Received August 11, 2004; revision requested November 8 and received December 22; accepted January 3, 2005. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose. P.J.S. supported by a grant from the British Heart Foundation.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Sparrow/Patrick+J" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">John B.</span> <span property="familyName">Kurian</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the British Heart Foundation Cardiac MRI Unit, Room 170, D Floor, Jubilee Wing, The General Infirmary, Leeds LS1 3EX, England. Received August 11, 2004; revision requested November 8 and received December 22; accepted January 3, 2005. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose. P.J.S. supported by a grant f